quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  19,83,"Dost thou not see that we have sent the devils against the misbelievers, to drive them on to sin"
  19,84,"but, be not thou hasty with them. Verily, we will number them a number (of days)"
  19,85,the day when we will gather the pious to the Merciful as ambassadors
  19,86,and we will drive the sinners to hell like (herds) to water
  19,87,"They shall not possess intercession, save he who has taken a compact with the Merciful"
  19,88,"They say, 'The Merciful has taken to Himself a son"
  19,89,ye have brought a monstrous thing
  19,90,"The heavens well-nigh burst asunder thereat, and the earth is riven, and the mountains fall down broken"
  19,91,that they attribute to the Merciful a son
  19,92,"but it, becomes not the Merciful to take to Himself a son"
  19,93,there is none in the heavens or the earth but comes to the Merciful as a servant
  19,94,He counts them and numbers them by number
  19,95,and they are all coming to Him on the resurrection day singly
  19,96,"Verily, those who believe and act aright, to them the Merciful will give love"
  19,97,"We have only made it easy for thy tongue that thou mayest thereby give glad tidings to the pious, and warn thereby a contentious people"
  19,98,"How many a Generation before them have we destroyed? Canst thou find any one of them, or hear a whisper of them"